Now, I'm done being nice to you, maggot! Now move!

799
00:49:57,204 --> 00:49:58,080
You okay, Cage?

800
00:49:58,163 --> 00:49:59,831
Oh, yeah! Yeah, I'm good! I'm good!

801
00:50:00,249 --> 00:50:01,250
You're leg's broken.

802
00:50:01,291 --> 00:50:03,585
No! I...I can still feel my toes.

803
00:50:05,587 --> 00:50:06,630
Oh, come on!

804
00:50:26,400 --> 00:50:29,361
Rita! Rita! What is this?
What are you doing here?

805
00:50:29,361 --> 00:50:30,779
Look, who's this guy?

806
00:50:30,862 --> 00:50:33,031
- He's me... before Verdun.
- ... before Verdun.

807
00:50:33,031 --> 00:50:34,241
What...what do you mean? He's...?

808
00:50:34,241 --> 00:50:35,242
Yes! Yes!

809
00:50:35,242 --> 00:50:36,410
When did he die? Where?

810
00:50:36,535 --> 00:50:37,786
On the beach, tomorrow.

811
00:50:37,828 --> 00:50:39,121
I'm Will Cage,
you're Dr. Carter.

812
00:50:39,121 --> 00:50:41,999
We've had this conversation before.
You have two fingers behind your back.

813
00:50:42,165 --> 00:50:43,333
I've had the visions.

814
00:50:43,584 --> 00:50:44,585
I've seen the Omega.

815
00:50:50,632 --> 00:50:53,635
It's... pretty much game over tomorrow,

816
00:50:53,677 --> 00:50:55,345
So can we move this along?

817
00:50:55,679 --> 00:50:56,680
Okay.

818
00:50:57,389 --> 00:50:58,390
Where?

819
00:50:59,224 --> 00:51:01,810
There's a dam,
it's in the mountains.

820
00:51:01,810 --> 00:51:02,811
I saw German writing.

821
00:51:03,228 --> 00:51:05,063
Do you think you can work out where that is?

822
00:51:05,063 --> 00:51:05,188
Well, I mean there can't be
too many places that fit that description.
Do you think you can work out where that is?

823
00:51:05,188 --> 00:51:08,525
Well, I mean there can't be
too many places that fit that description.

824
00:51:08,525 --> 00:51:09,818
I'll see what I can do.

825
00:51:10,402 --> 00:51:11,486
Training's over.

826
00:51:11,862 --> 00:51:12,988
I'll see you tomorrow.

827
00:51:13,280 --> 00:51:15,949
- We don't even know where we're going.
- We will, soon enough.

828
00:51:16,742 --> 00:51:19,536
In the mean time, you need to figure out
a way to get us off that beach.

829
00:51:41,725 --> 00:51:43,644
What next?
Where are we going?

830
00:51:43,644 --> 00:51:45,312
- Yeah...
- Which way? Focus!

831
00:51:45,354 --> 00:51:46,021
Which way?

832
00:51:46,021 --> 00:51:47,022
I'm thinking.
I'm thinking.

833
00:51:47,105 --> 00:51:47,940
Okay...

834
00:51:48,065 --> 00:51:48,857
Oh, man!

835
00:51:49,608 --> 00:51:50,984
How far do we make it?

836
00:51:51,193 --> 00:51:54,780
Well, it's... hard to say.

837
00:51:56,490 --> 00:51:57,366
Hold!

838
00:51:57,658 --> 00:51:58,367
Hold!

839
00:51:58,992 --> 00:51:59,952
Okay, go!

840
00:52:01,787 --> 00:52:02,913
Son of a bitch!

841
00:52:03,080 --> 00:52:04,998
- I thought stepping left, ducking.
- Fine.

842
00:52:04,998 --> 00:52:06,124
Just for the record, stepping left...

843
00:52:06,124 --> 00:52:08,210
- Stepping left, ducking right.
- It was pretty specific.

844
00:52:08,543 --> 00:52:10,796
Stepping left, ducking right.

845
00:52:11,338 --> 00:52:11,964
Move on.

846
00:52:15,384 --> 00:52:16,426
Hold on!

847
00:52:16,760 --> 00:52:19,763
Now remember, across the trench, twelve o'clock,

848
00:52:19,930 --> 00:52:20,889
then look to your right.

849
00:52:28,105 --> 00:52:30,023
- You're not being specific, you understand?
- Oh, okay.

850
00:52:30,023 --> 00:52:32,609
You need to be specific,
otherwise I'm dead.

851
00:52:32,901 --> 00:52:33,610
Rita.

852
00:52:35,821 --> 00:52:36,613
Cage!

853
00:52:38,782 --> 00:52:40,867
That takes us up to the top and then the trench.

854
00:52:40,867 --> 00:52:43,495
I'm gonna step left, there's gonna be
a Mimic there which I'll kill...

855
00:52:53,338 --> 00:52:55,924
There's an explosion, I'm gonna run
thirty paces to the north west.

856
00:52:55,924 --> 00:52:59,052
I'm gonna duck at the top of that trench,
and then I'm gonna turn left.

857
00:53:08,604 --> 00:53:10,022
I got something on my face?

858
00:53:12,649 --> 00:53:13,358
No!

859
00:53:21,575 --> 00:53:22,367
<i>Cage!</i>

860
00:53:22,910 --> 00:53:24,328
<i>We've been looking everywhere for you!</i>

861
00:53:25,579 --> 00:53:26,163
Cage!

862
00:53:28,790 --> 00:53:29,499
Guys.

863
00:53:29,708 --> 00:53:32,252
Guys can we just...

864
00:53:32,544 --> 00:53:34,379
not do this today?

865
00:53:34,630 --> 00:53:35,839
What are you talking about?

866
00:53:36,465 --> 00:53:39,259
Farell almost strung us up
by our bullocks for losing track of you!

867
00:53:41,637 --> 00:53:42,721
Okay, Skinner.

868
00:53:42,930 --> 00:53:43,931
Watch this.

869
00:53:45,182 --> 00:53:46,600
Now I'm gonna close my eyes.

870
00:53:47,351 --> 00:53:48,435
- Ready?
- Yeah.

871
00:53:56,485 --> 00:53:58,362
I didn't mind the extra push ups.

872
00:54:08,538 --> 00:54:09,790
<i>It's a new day, people!</i>

873
00:54:10,832 --> 00:54:12,084
Destiny calls.

874
00:54:12,501 --> 00:54:14,753
The world expects only one thing from us:

875
00:54:14,878 --> 00:54:15,879
That we will win!

876
00:54:31,520 --> 00:54:35,691
<i>The current situation on the front line
show heavy casualties...</i>

877
00:54:36,358 --> 00:54:38,610
<i>It's about time we showed
those things what we're made of. </i>

878
00:54:38,902 --> 00:54:41,238
<i>My father flew in the battle of Britain,</i>

879
00:54:41,488 --> 00:54:44,074
<i>three years before the yanks came into the war.</i>

880
00:54:44,825 --> 00:54:47,744
Couldn't be broken, backbone.

881
00:54:47,911 --> 00:54:50,289
My Uncle George landed
on the beach of Normandy, yeah.

882
00:54:50,789 --> 00:54:54,251
In their day, this war
would have been over by now.

883
00:54:54,459 --> 00:54:56,086
What do they want with us anyway?

884
00:54:56,545 --> 00:54:58,171
It's obvious, isn't it?
Minerals.

885
00:54:58,297 --> 00:54:59,131
Minerals?

886
00:54:59,131 --> 00:55:00,549
- Yeah, minerals.
- Oxygen, they want.

887
00:55:00,966 --> 00:55:01,425
Oxygen?

888
00:55:01,425 --> 00:55:01,717
Think about it...

889
00:55:01,842 --> 00:55:02,676
What difference does it make?

890
00:55:03,927 --> 00:55:05,637
They're here, they're winning.

891
00:55:06,346 --> 00:55:08,890
And whatever it is, they're gonna get it.

892
00:55:09,391 --> 00:55:10,642
Shouldn't you be over there?

893
00:55:12,060 --> 00:55:13,061
I've been over there.

894
00:55:14,271 --> 00:55:15,606
More times than anybody.

895
00:55:16,440 --> 00:55:20,152
As a matter of fact,
I'm usually long dead by now.

896
00:55:23,113 --> 00:55:24,072
Coward.

897
00:55:27,576 --> 00:55:30,495
- What's going on?
- The power's gone.

898
00:56:38,772 --> 00:56:41,400
I found the Omega. I found it.
It has to be here.

899
00:56:41,733 --> 00:56:43,610
Groer Dam, Germany.
This as got to be it.

900
00:56:43,610 --> 00:56:44,695
It fits the description perfectly.

901
00:56:44,820 --> 00:56:46,196
Yes, you found it.

902
00:56:46,321 --> 00:56:47,322
Again.

903
00:56:47,906 --> 00:56:51,994
What difference does it make?
Cause we're never gonna get there.

904
00:56:52,869 --> 00:56:54,246
No matter what we do,

905
00:56:55,080 --> 00:56:57,541
no matter how carefully we plan,

906
00:56:58,500 --> 00:57:00,127
we can't get off that beach.

907
00:57:10,887 --> 00:57:13,432
You can do this.
You can.

908
00:57:13,724 --> 00:57:16,602
You keep coming here everyday
and I'll train you.

909
00:57:19,771 --> 00:57:21,148
You already have.

910
00:57:40,709 --> 00:57:41,627
I'm waiting, Nance!

911
00:57:41,752 --> 00:57:43,587
Five hundred meters and closing fast!

912
00:57:44,838 --> 00:57:45,672
What the...?!

913
00:57:54,973 --> 00:57:55,724
<i>Reloading.</i>

914
00:58:07,903 --> 00:58:08,820
What's next?

915
00:58:11,073 --> 00:58:12,282
Straight shot.

916
00:58:12,866 --> 00:58:13,575
Up the hill.

917
00:58:13,951 --> 00:58:14,826
Okay.

918
00:58:15,786 --> 00:58:16,828
Hey, Serge.

919
00:58:16,995 --> 00:58:17,996
The new guy,...

920
00:58:18,789 --> 00:58:20,082
what's his name again?

921
00:58:24,002 --> 00:58:26,380
We need a vehicle to get further inland.

922
00:58:26,838 --> 00:58:27,714
Then what's the problem?

923
00:58:27,839 --> 00:58:32,469
The problem is the ambush waiting for us down there,
they kill before we find a working car.

924
00:58:32,678 --> 00:58:34,429
Okay, so what's the current plan?

925
00:58:34,805 --> 00:58:37,182
- The two cars I haven't tried are the Minivan...
- Yep.

926
00:58:37,182 --> 00:58:38,475
- and the green SUV.
- Okay.

927
00:58:39,476 --> 00:58:42,312
I'll head for the SUV, draw the Mimics to me.
You go for the Minivan.

928
00:58:42,437 --> 00:58:44,648
You get it started, just go, take off.

929
00:58:44,773 --> 00:58:46,483
- Do not wait for me.
- Okay.

930
00:58:48,318 --> 00:58:51,029
Well...just don't forget to disconnect
the caravan before you take off.

931
00:58:51,154 --> 00:58:52,406
You are going to be in a hurry,

932
00:58:52,614 --> 00:58:54,366
you don't want any dead weight.

933
00:59:19,766 --> 00:59:20,601
Come on.

934
00:59:35,866 --> 00:59:36,867
Come on, Cage!

935
00:59:43,457 --> 00:59:44,333
Can't see!

936
00:59:46,501 --> 00:59:47,586
Did you...?

937
00:59:56,470 --> 00:59:58,680
<i>Stay where you are, remain calm.</i>

938
00:59:59,306 --> 01:00:03,018
<i> If you are in a vehicle,
please lock the doors and stay inside.</i>

939
01:00:11,610 --> 01:00:13,654
<i>The enemy has reached London.</i>

940
01:00:13,779 --> 01:00:14,321
<i> Repeat.</i>

941
01:00:14,529 --> 01:00:16,448
<i>London is under attack.</i>

942
01:00:21,453 --> 01:00:22,537
That's good driving.

943
01:00:22,955 --> 01:00:24,831
I forgot to unhook the trailer.

944
01:01:10,669 --> 01:01:12,296
You don't talk much.

945
01:01:13,422 --> 01:01:14,506
Not a fan.

946
01:01:15,007 --> 01:01:15,841
Of talking?

947
01:01:16,550 --> 01:01:18,135
Not a fan of talking, no.

948
01:01:20,012 --> 01:01:21,888
You know, you eventually do talk to me.

949
01:01:24,308 --> 01:01:27,728
It's usually around Lyon, you tell me
about the time you went there with your family.

950
01:01:28,312 --> 01:01:29,813
Your brother got lost.

951
01:01:31,899 --> 01:01:33,775
I've never been to Lyon.

952
01:01:34,401 --> 01:01:36,069
You tell me your middle name.

953
01:01:37,654 --> 01:01:38,697
Peyton.

954
01:01:41,074 --> 01:01:42,284
That's not my middle name.

955
01:01:47,915 --> 01:01:50,042
You found your brother in the arcade, by the way.

956
01:01:52,419 --> 01:01:54,796
Well maybe I made it all up just to keep you quiet.

957
01:01:55,005 --> 01:01:55,839
But you do talk to me.

958
01:01:56,256 --> 01:01:58,216
Cage, I do not need to get to know you.

959
01:01:58,300 --> 01:02:01,094
And if you knew what was good for you,
you wouldn't want to get to know me either.

960
01:02:01,595 --> 01:02:03,597
It's the only way you make it through this thing.

961
01:02:04,932 --> 01:02:06,892
What about Hendricks, you get to know him?

962
01:02:07,768 --> 01:02:08,894
How do you know that name?

963
01:02:09,019 --> 01:02:10,395
You mention him.

964
01:02:10,896 --> 01:02:12,022
That's not possible.

965
01:02:12,356 --> 01:02:14,316
- Then how do I know his name?
- When did I mention him?

966
01:02:14,316 --> 01:02:15,317
Under what circumstance?

967
01:02:17,527 --> 01:02:19,529
Is he why you won't talk to me?

968
01:02:23,242 --> 01:02:25,285
Don't ever mention his name again.

969
01:02:26,787 --> 01:02:27,996
Why...

970
01:02:27,996 --> 01:02:28,997
- are you in love with him?
- He's dead!

971
01:02:33,085 --> 01:02:34,962
And I watched him die three hundred times,

972
01:02:35,087 --> 01:02:38,840
and I remember... every detail,
I remember everything.

973
01:02:38,966 --> 01:02:41,009
So I don't need to talk about it.

974
01:02:46,306 --> 01:02:47,432
I'm sorry.

975
01:02:47,891 --> 01:02:48,892
It's just war.

976
01:03:52,497 --> 01:03:54,541
There's nothing here, keep going.

977
01:04:18,190 --> 01:04:19,483
We have to find the keys.

978
01:04:20,859 --> 01:04:22,110
Let's just siphon the gas.

979
01:04:22,236 --> 01:04:24,279
And why drive when we can fly?

980
01:04:24,988 --> 01:04:26,114
In that thing?

981
01:04:26,240 --> 01:04:28,075
Let me guess, you're afraid of heights.

982
01:04:28,200 --> 01:04:29,743
I'm afraid of crashing.

983
01:04:30,077 --> 01:04:31,578
I'm not at all ashamed to admit it.

984
01:04:31,703 --> 01:04:33,914
You'll be fine, Cage.
You'll learn.

985
01:04:35,707 --> 01:04:37,876
- What is it?
-  It's nothing, I'm fine.

986
01:04:38,919 --> 01:04:40,254
- What is it?
- It's nothing.

987
01:04:40,837 --> 01:04:41,546
Rita.

988
01:04:45,676 --> 01:04:46,593
Let me see.

989
01:05:07,072 --> 01:05:09,032
We have to find the keys to the helicopter.

990
01:05:09,283 --> 01:05:10,826
I'm sure they're around here somewhere.

991
01:05:11,827 --> 01:05:13,495
You know the heli's full of fuel,

992
01:05:13,829 --> 01:05:15,205
I found a hose.

993
01:05:16,123 --> 01:05:17,332
We're flying, Cage.

994
01:05:21,753 --> 01:05:24,464
Well, let's just say we find keys, you know?

995
01:05:25,257 --> 01:05:26,842
Get that helicopter started.

996
01:05:27,467 --> 01:05:29,428
We don't have our jackets or ammunition.

997
01:05:29,845 --> 01:05:31,638
And it's gonna be dark in a few hours.

998
01:05:34,349 --> 01:05:36,810
Might be better just going back to the farmhouse,

999
01:05:37,185 --> 01:05:41,106
seeing what we could salvage.
You know, spend the night there.

1000
01:05:41,648 --> 01:05:42,691
Come back here in the morning.

1001
01:05:42,774 --> 01:05:45,652
And curl up by the fire
and open a bottle of wine?

1002
01:05:49,531 --> 01:05:51,033
We should just reset.

1003
01:05:51,950 --> 01:05:53,243
- It's a dead end.
- Hey, hold...just...

1004
01:05:53,368 --> 01:05:54,453
If it's all the same to you,

1005
01:05:54,703 --> 01:05:57,331
I'm tired, I'm in pain.
I'd rather just start fresh.

1006
01:05:57,539 --> 01:06:00,000
I'll tell you what, take a few minutes.
Coffee's ready.

1007
01:06:00,584 --> 01:06:02,210
I'll look around for the keys, that's productive.

1008
01:06:02,502 --> 01:06:03,420
Ten minutes.

1009
01:06:03,712 --> 01:06:04,171
Okay.

1010
01:06:04,421 --> 01:06:05,631
And then I'm killing you.

1011
01:06:06,548 --> 01:06:07,382
Fine.

1012
01:06:11,219 --> 01:06:12,679
I can't believe you found coffee.

1013
01:06:15,057 --> 01:06:15,974
Thank you.

1014
01:06:19,770 --> 01:06:20,729
Oh. Sugar, right?

1015
01:06:21,188 --> 01:06:21,813
Yeah.

1016
01:06:27,861 --> 01:06:28,570
Thank you.

1017
01:06:28,779 --> 01:06:29,780
Hold on, three.

1018
01:06:29,988 --> 01:06:30,989
You like three.

1019
01:06:44,753 --> 01:06:46,964
There's a shirt over there,
it should be your size.

1020
01:06:55,514 --> 01:06:57,349
How many times have we been here?

1021
01:07:03,897 --> 01:07:05,065
How many times?

1022
01:07:06,275 --> 01:07:07,484
Where are the keys?

1023
01:07:09,027 --> 01:07:10,445
- Where are the Goddamn keys?
-  Okay.

1024
01:07:13,824 --> 01:07:15,534
You can fly it, can't you?

1025
01:07:15,701 --> 01:07:16,910
No. Well...yes.

1026
01:07:16,910 --> 01:07:19,871
I mean, I can take off,
I'm still working on my landing.

1027
01:07:19,871 --> 01:07:21,832
What are we still doing here?
You're wasting time!

1028
01:07:22,291 --> 01:07:22,791
Rita.

1029
01:07:22,791 --> 01:07:24,293
You start that engine, you die!

1030
01:07:28,463 --> 01:07:29,923
This is as far as you go.

1031
01:07:30,382 --> 01:07:31,717
No matter what I do.

1032
01:07:32,926 --> 01:07:34,678
This is as far as you ever make it.

1033
01:07:43,020 --> 01:07:45,856
There's a Mimic buried twenty yards away.

1034
01:07:46,356 --> 01:07:48,233
It attacks when you start the engine.

1035
01:07:49,776 --> 01:07:51,987
Get your weapon
and get in the helicopter, Cage.

1036
01:07:52,321 --> 01:07:54,114
There's more than a field battle there.

1037
01:07:56,742 --> 01:07:58,201
Only one of us ever makes it.

1038
01:07:58,410 --> 01:07:58,911
Get in.

1039
01:07:59,119 --> 01:08:01,914
The only thing we haven't tried is a version
where you walk away, just go back to the farmhouse.

1040
01:08:02,039 --> 01:08:05,375
There's food, you wait there until I get back.

1041
01:08:05,500 --> 01:08:06,501
You'll be safe.

1042
01:08:06,627 --> 01:08:08,795
I'm a soldier,
I volunteered.

1043
01:08:08,837 --> 01:08:09,838
I'm not walking away.

1044
01:08:09,963 --> 01:08:11,089
You die here!

1045
01:08:11,506 --> 01:08:12,299
Right here!

1046
01:08:14,718 --> 01:08:15,844
I...can't save you.

1047
01:08:16,511 --> 01:08:18,722
And if I go on and kill the Omega.

1048
01:08:18,889 --> 01:08:19,890
You're dead.

1049
01:08:20,432 --> 01:08:21,099
Forever.

1050
01:08:21,558 --> 01:08:23,435
Why does it matter what happens to me?

1051
01:08:27,439 --> 01:08:30,484
I wish I didn't know you.

1052
01:08:33,028 --> 01:08:33,987
But I do.

1053
01:10:05,454 --> 01:10:07,080
My middle name...

1054
01:10:08,332 --> 01:10:09,333
is Rose.

1055
01:10:29,895 --> 01:10:31,521
On your feet, maggot!

1056
01:10:43,033 --> 01:10:44,993
<i>Looks there's hope for your, Private. </i>

1057
01:10:45,118 --> 01:10:47,412
<i>Hope in the form of glorious combat.</i>

1058
01:10:48,247 --> 01:10:49,623
<i>Battle is the great redeemer.</i>

1059
01:10:49,873 --> 01:10:52,000
<i>the fire and crucible
in which the only true heroes are forged. </i>

1060
01:10:52,000 --> 01:10:53,001
<i>The one place...</i>

1061
01:11:04,972 --> 01:11:05,764
Yes?

1062
01:11:07,057 --> 01:11:08,684
Who said you could talk to me?

1063
01:11:12,646 --> 01:11:14,481
Do I have something on my face, soldier?

1064
01:11:18,193 --> 01:11:19,736
I'm sorry to disturb you, Sergeant.

1065
01:11:42,217 --> 01:11:44,469
Alright, man. Let's get this show on the road.
I gotta suite up.

1066
01:11:47,556 --> 01:11:48,724
Where's your helmet?

1067
01:11:50,434 --> 01:11:51,810
I'm not gonna wear one.

1068
01:11:52,269 --> 01:11:53,520
It's a distraction.

1069
01:11:56,189 --> 01:11:56,940
Have you been drinking?

1070
01:11:56,940 --> 01:11:59,610
I need three more clips of five-five-six,

1071
01:11:59,651 --> 01:12:02,112
eight grenades and an extra battery.

1072
01:12:06,283 --> 01:12:07,200
Get it!

1073
01:12:14,249 --> 01:12:15,083
Oy!

1074
01:12:15,250 --> 01:12:16,251
Oy, mate!

1075
01:12:17,377 --> 01:12:19,087
I think there's something wrong with your suite!

1076
01:12:20,672 --> 01:12:22,007
There's a dead guy in it.

1077
01:12:23,133 --> 01:12:24,051
<i>Yeah!</i>

1078
01:12:24,384 --> 01:12:24,968
Wooh-hoo! We made it!

1079
01:12:24,968 --> 01:12:27,304
Thank God, we made it!
Yeah...!

1080
01:14:29,927 --> 01:14:30,928
Finish it!

1081
01:15:25,566 --> 01:15:27,150
It isn't there.

1082
01:15:27,359 --> 01:15:28,860
What do you mean
the Omega isn't there?

1083
01:15:28,860 --> 01:15:30,195
My guess is it never was.

1084
01:15:30,279 --> 01:15:31,613
They knew we were coming.

1085
01:15:31,780 --> 01:15:34,157
They ambushed us.
The visions were a trap.

1086
01:15:35,701 --> 01:15:38,203
Just like Rita's visions were a trap at Verdun.

1087
01:15:39,955 --> 01:15:41,498
It could have killed me, but it didn't.

1088
01:15:41,873 --> 01:15:42,791
It's after my blood.

1089
01:15:43,000 --> 01:15:44,543
So they know who you are, they...

1090
01:15:46,211 --> 01:15:47,170
They want their power back.

1091
01:15:47,170 --> 01:15:48,880
And they're gonna get it one way or another,

1092
01:15:48,880 --> 01:15:50,799
unless we find the Omega.

1093
01:15:51,633 --> 01:15:53,093
There...there isn't any other way, we're finished!

1094
01:15:53,218 --> 01:15:54,887
No, we're not finished.

1095
01:15:55,470 --> 01:15:56,680
It doesn't work.
I can't get it to work...

1096
01:15:56,722 --> 01:16:00,392
- You built a prototype at Whitehall.
- Yes! And I got fired for it, thank you very much.

1097
01:16:01,226 --> 01:16:02,895
- What is this thing, anyway?
- It's a transponder.

1098
01:16:02,895 --> 01:16:06,523
You stick it into the Alpha and it taps
into the wavelength connecting it to the Omega.

1099
01:16:06,523 --> 01:16:08,025
That's the idea anyway.

1100
01:16:08,358 --> 01:16:11,236
But I can't get it to work,
not with the equipment I have on hand.

1101
01:16:13,864 --> 01:16:15,073
How do we get you what you need?

1102
01:16:15,198 --> 01:16:16,533
Well, that's the thing. I mean,...

1103
01:16:16,533 --> 01:16:19,536
when I was at Whitehall I built one,
I was even ready to test it,

1104
01:16:19,786 --> 01:16:21,204
but when I told my superiors about it,

1105
01:16:21,204 --> 01:16:22,205
well I lost my job.

1106
01:16:22,331 --> 01:16:23,916
They thought he was crazy.

1107
01:16:24,291 --> 01:16:25,918
So all we need to do is go to Whitehall.

1108
01:16:26,460 --> 01:16:28,921
He'd be arrested ten feet from the front doors.

1109
01:16:29,046 --> 01:16:30,672
Psyche ward dissection, remember?

1110
01:16:31,798 --> 01:16:32,966
Hey, hey, hey! Aren't you forgetting something?

1111
01:16:33,258 --> 01:16:35,969
The transponder requires
a live Alpha to make it work.

1112
01:16:36,094 --> 01:16:37,429
We don't need one.

1113
01:16:38,096 --> 01:16:39,681
We got the next best thing.

1114
01:16:43,060 --> 01:16:45,896
When the Chinese delegation comes out,
you pick up the pace.

1115
01:16:48,232 --> 01:16:50,901
There's a guy with a yellow arm band
that always recognizes you.

1116
01:16:51,026 --> 01:16:53,654
So just keep your head down
and stay to my right.

1117
01:17:00,452 --> 01:17:02,037
Nicely done.

1118
01:17:05,040 --> 01:17:05,374
One.

1119
01:17:05,582 --> 01:17:06,291
Two.

1120
01:17:06,500 --> 01:17:07,501
Hold.

1121
01:17:22,015 --> 01:17:22,683
Turn.

1122
01:17:23,559 --> 01:17:25,644
Okay, keep walking.
Just go straight ahead.

1123
01:17:27,354 --> 01:17:28,772
<i> Robinson</i>

1124
01:17:29,481 --> 01:17:31,108
I've asked not to be disturbed.

1125
01:17:31,191 --> 01:17:32,317
This had better be critical.

1126
01:17:32,568 --> 01:17:33,652
Fate of mankind.

1127
01:17:33,777 --> 01:17:34,861
Critical enough?

1128
01:17:35,612 --> 01:17:36,905
I don't believe what I'm seeing.

1129
01:17:37,030 --> 01:17:38,740
I've had more than my share of that.

1130
01:17:39,616 --> 01:17:41,660
Sit down, General,
and stay away from your desk.

1131
01:17:42,619 --> 01:17:44,746
I'd take her very seriously if I were you.

1132
01:17:46,582 --> 01:17:48,208
I have to hand it to you, Major.

1133
01:17:49,126 --> 01:17:51,795
when you left this office today,
I never imagined you'd be back,

1134
01:17:51,795 --> 01:17:53,922
let alone with my most decorated soldier.

1135
01:17:54,047 --> 01:17:55,424
I'm here to tell you a story, General.

1136
01:17:55,507 --> 01:17:58,844
and at first it's gonna sound ridiculous,
but the longer I talk the more rational,

1137
01:17:58,844 --> 01:17:59,720
it's going to appear.

1138
01:17:59,720 --> 01:18:01,221
Tell him you'll call back.

1139
01:18:01,597 --> 01:18:02,264
Tell who?

1140
01:18:02,472 --> 01:18:04,266
Major General Beaumont calling from Halifax,

1141
01:18:04,266 --> 01:18:05,475
His plane's just been delayed.

1142
01:18:05,684 --> 01:18:06,310
Bad weather.

1143
01:18:07,144 --> 01:18:07,769
Yes?

1144
01:18:11,398 --> 01:18:13,066
Thank you, Beaumont.
I'll call you back.

1145
01:18:15,903 --> 01:18:17,321
Tomorrow's invasion is a slaughter.

1146
01:18:17,446 --> 01:18:21,158
I'm dead within five minutes of landing on that beach,
along with every other soldier you are sending.

1147
01:18:21,491 --> 01:18:23,869
And that's because
the enemy knows we're coming.

1148
01:18:24,286 --> 01:18:25,579
Now how do I know this?

1149
01:18:25,787 --> 01:18:27,289
Before I died I killed a Mimic,

1150
01:18:27,289 --> 01:18:28,290
only this one was different.

1151
01:18:28,665 --> 01:18:30,667
It passed something
onto me in my blood.

1152
01:18:30,792 --> 01:18:33,337
Now I relive the same day
over and over again.

1153
01:18:33,462 --> 01:18:34,755
Just like they do.

1154
01:18:34,880 --> 01:18:37,174
Just like Sergeant Vrataski at Verdun.

1155
01:18:37,591 --> 01:18:39,384
Tell your secretary everything's fine.

1156
01:18:40,469 --> 01:18:41,678
I beg your pardon?

1157
01:18:44,973 --> 01:18:47,142
Oh, I'm sorry, General.
I thought you were alone.

1158
01:18:47,267 --> 01:18:47,976
It's fine.

1159
01:18:48,393 --> 01:18:50,354
She typed up those orders for you to authorize,

1160
01:18:50,479 --> 01:18:52,898
but she left out the word
eferring to the fuel duct in Greenwich.

1161
01:18:55,484 --> 01:18:56,443
Your name is Iris.

1162
01:18:56,693 --> 01:18:58,237
You're birthday is September 17th.

1163
01:18:59,279 --> 01:19:02,574
The General probably pulled some
strings stationed your only son in Australia,

1164
01:19:02,574 --> 01:19:04,284
as far from the war as possible.

1165
01:19:04,409 --> 01:19:07,120
Tell the General his dinner's been canceled,
the call came in just now.

1166
01:19:09,331 --> 01:19:10,916
Your dinner was canceled.

1167
01:19:11,500 --> 01:19:13,418
You forgot the fuel duct.

1168
01:19:14,253 --> 01:19:16,213
Thank you, Iris.
That will be all.

1169
01:19:24,012 --> 01:19:26,473
- Cage, Let's go.
- Rita.

1170
01:19:26,598 --> 01:19:27,849
- Let me just...
- What are you doing?

1171
01:19:28,100 --> 01:19:29,142
Please, don't shoot him yet.

1172
01:19:29,893 --> 01:19:31,270
Okay? Just...

1173
01:19:35,607 --> 01:19:36,275
General.

1174
01:19:36,608 --> 01:19:39,069
Th...this isn't the first time
we've had this conversation.

1175
01:19:39,069 --> 01:19:42,406
Cause that's...because you're...you're stubborn.

1176
01:19:43,365 --> 01:19:46,118
You won't believe me when I tell you
that Dr. Carter was right,

1177
01:19:46,118 --> 01:19:49,037
That the enemy can manipulate time.

1178
01:19:49,246 --> 01:19:50,205
The invasion will fail,

1179
01:19:50,414 --> 01:19:52,958
no matter how many bodies you throw at it.

1180
01:19:53,125 --> 01:19:54,793
And the only way to win this war,

1181
01:19:54,793 --> 01:19:57,838
is by finding this power source within the cord

1182
01:19:57,838 --> 01:19:58,755
and killing it.

1183
01:19:58,755 --> 01:20:00,716
And the only means of finding it

1184
01:20:00,882 --> 01:20:02,426
is in that safe right there.

1185
01:20:04,636 --> 01:20:06,972
No matter how many times
that we have this conversation,

1186
01:20:07,222 --> 01:20:10,309
you refuse to accept that the enemy
breaks through to London tomorrow,

1187
01:20:10,434 --> 01:20:11,685
and we lose.

1188
01:20:11,894 --> 01:20:12,895
We lose everything.

1189
01:20:20,986 --> 01:20:22,404
Let's say for the moment,

1190
01:20:23,822 --> 01:20:25,616
that I can't rationally explain...

1191
01:20:26,950 --> 01:20:28,827
your impressive parlor tricks.

1192
01:20:31,288 --> 01:20:33,332
Dr. Carter told me...

1193
01:20:33,999 --> 01:20:36,209
this device requires a live Mimic to work.

1194
01:20:36,418 --> 01:20:37,419
What use is it to you?

1195
01:20:38,503 --> 01:20:40,464
- That's my concern.
- On the contrary.

1196
01:20:40,881 --> 01:20:43,175
According to you, this concerns the whole world.

1197
01:20:43,550 --> 01:20:46,511
Well what would you do if you believed
everything I just told you?

1198
01:20:48,305 --> 01:20:50,224
- I would locate this...
- Omega.

1199
01:20:50,349 --> 01:20:51,683
And bomb it out of existence.

1200
01:20:51,725 --> 01:20:53,560
You're not mentally equipped
to fight this thing,

1201
01:20:53,685 --> 01:20:54,728
and you never will be.

1202
01:21:12,329 --> 01:21:13,914
What do we do now?

1203
01:21:14,831 --> 01:21:16,541
I don't know.
We've never gotten this far.

1204
01:21:23,757 --> 01:21:24,633
That was easy.

1205
01:21:24,841 --> 01:21:26,134
Stop! Stop right there!

1206
01:21:26,343 --> 01:21:27,177
Don't move!

1207
01:21:27,469 --> 01:21:28,428
Nobody move!

1208
01:21:30,389 --> 01:21:31,098
Drop it!

1209
01:21:40,148 --> 01:21:41,233
How am I supposed to do this?

1210
01:21:41,233 --> 01:21:42,234
Stick it in your leg!

1211
01:21:42,901 --> 01:21:43,652
Do it!

1212
01:22:02,212 --> 01:22:03,505
<i>Cage, what happened?</i>

1213
01:22:04,715 --> 01:22:05,674
<i>Talk to me!</i>

1214
01:22:06,383 --> 01:22:08,802
<i> I feel it, it...it's taking me there.</i>

1215
01:22:09,553 --> 01:22:10,762
<i>What do you see?</i>

1216
01:22:12,681 --> 01:22:14,016
<i>It's...it's the Louvre.</i>

1217
01:22:14,141 --> 01:22:15,392
<i>Where? Where else?</i>

1218
01:22:16,059 --> 01:22:18,103
<i>I'm inside now. It's flooded.</i>

1219
01:22:19,313 --> 01:22:22,482
<i>I'm going down a garage,
a garage underneath the museum.</i>

1220
01:22:22,774 --> 01:22:24,234
<i<The Omega, do you see it?

1221
01:22:31,158 --> 01:22:32,159
It's in Paris!

1222
01:22:50,052 --> 01:22:50,719
Rita!

1223
01:23:32,553 --> 01:23:34,054
What have you done?

1224
01:23:34,596 --> 01:23:35,973
What have you done?

1225
01:23:38,475 --> 01:23:40,686
You'll be fine.
You just needed blood.

1226
01:23:41,270 --> 01:23:43,272
You don't know what you've just done.

1227
01:23:43,689 --> 01:23:45,274
I'm not allowed to talk to you.

1228
01:23:45,399 --> 01:23:46,858
I was with someone.

1229
01:23:48,819 --> 01:23:50,654
Rita Vrataski. Is she alive?

1230
01:23:51,363 --> 01:23:52,614
Rita Vrataski?

1231
01:23:53,282 --> 01:23:54,074
Please.

1232
01:23:55,158 --> 01:23:56,118
Just tell me that.

1233
01:23:58,954 --> 01:24:00,080
Please tell me.

1234
01:24:01,206 --> 01:24:01,957
I'm sorry.

1235
01:24:39,283 --> 01:24:41,535
I was out of those things in three minutes flat, Cage.

1236
01:24:41,535 --> 01:24:42,452
What's wrong with you?

1237
01:24:44,246 --> 01:24:45,622
I thought you were dead.

1238
01:24:46,373 --> 01:24:47,249
Not yet.

1239
01:24:52,588 --> 01:24:53,505
I'm sorry, Cage.

1240
01:24:53,714 --> 01:24:54,715
No! Wait, wait, wait!

1241
01:24:54,756 --> 01:24:56,425
I'm out! I'm out!

1242
01:24:56,592 --> 01:24:57,593
They gave me blood!

1243
01:25:02,097 --> 01:25:03,140
I lost the power.

1244
01:25:05,434 --> 01:25:06,310
I feel it.

1245
01:25:07,686 --> 01:25:09,480
I can't reset the day anymore.

1246
01:25:24,703 --> 01:25:25,954
We have to kill the Omega,

1247
01:25:26,413 --> 01:25:27,998
before the invasion starts.

1248
01:25:29,041 --> 01:25:30,626
That gives us less than three hours.

1249
01:25:31,793 --> 01:25:34,254
We need a drop ship to get to Paris in time.

1250
01:25:35,339 --> 01:25:36,840
We need more soldiers too.

1251
01:25:37,382 --> 01:25:39,551
No one's crazy enough to follow us to Paris.

1252
01:25:46,683 --> 01:25:47,392
Cage!

1253
01:25:47,976 --> 01:25:48,560
Cage!

1254
01:25:48,977 --> 01:25:49,520
Guys!

1255
01:25:49,520 --> 01:25:50,395
We've been looking everywhere for you!

1256
01:25:51,021 --> 01:25:51,855
Just listen...

1257
01:25:52,064 --> 01:25:54,566
Farell almost strung us up by our bullocks
for losing track of you!

1258
01:25:54,817 --> 01:25:55,818
Just listen.

1259
01:25:56,193 --> 01:25:57,903
But you're gonna want to hear this story.

1260
01:25:58,028 --> 01:26:02,241
Now it's gonna sound ridiculous at first,
but the longer I talk the more rational it's going to appear.

1261
01:26:02,658 --> 01:26:03,325
Yeah?!

1262
01:26:03,617 --> 01:26:05,244
He named the school I went to,

1263
01:26:05,994 --> 01:26:08,622
and then he tells me
my second grade teacher

1264
01:26:08,831 --> 01:26:10,082
was called Miss Pollyhook.

1265
01:26:10,165 --> 01:26:12,251
She wouldn't let him go to the bathroom,
made his wet his pants.

1266
01:26:13,126 --> 01:26:14,044
Shut up!

1267
01:26:14,837 --> 01:26:18,006
Look, I'm telling you, he know everything...

1268
01:26:18,882 --> 01:26:19,842
about all of us.

1269
01:26:19,925 --> 01:26:20,759
Bullshit.

1270
01:26:21,510 --> 01:26:22,177
Yeah?

1271
01:26:22,594 --> 01:26:24,847
He says your name ain't really Ford.

1272
01:26:25,681 --> 01:26:27,349
He says Ford was your friend,

1273
01:26:27,474 --> 01:26:29,268
died in combat on his first day.

1274
01:26:29,685 --> 01:26:32,229
You took his place,
send your checks to his family.

1275
01:26:32,563 --> 01:26:34,565
You slippery bitch.

1276
01:26:34,982 --> 01:26:36,692
Cage says the enemy knows us too.

1277
01:26:36,900 --> 01:26:38,402
They're waiting for us on the beach,

1278
01:26:38,652 --> 01:26:39,611
and we all die.

1279
01:26:39,695 --> 01:26:41,196
The whole invasion is a slaughter.

1280
01:26:58,406 --> 01:27:00,950
But it means coming with me, right now.

1281
01:27:01,368 --> 01:27:02,410
Listen, pal.

1282
01:27:02,619 --> 01:27:05,330
I don't really care
what you think you know about us.

1283
01:27:05,747 --> 01:27:06,956
We just met you.

1284
01:27:08,750 --> 01:27:10,877
Come on, why would we
follow him into combat?

1285
01:27:15,966 --> 01:27:17,467
I don't expect you to follow me.

1286
01:27:18,343 --> 01:27:19,844
I expect you to follow her.

1287
01:27:24,391 --> 01:27:25,517
That's the full metal bi...

1288
01:27:25,517 --> 01:27:26,184
J Squad.

1289
01:27:27,686 --> 01:27:28,937
This is Rita Vrataski.

1290
01:27:29,854 --> 01:27:30,689
Otherwise known as...

1291
01:27:30,689 --> 01:27:31,731
Yeah, yeah.

1292
01:27:32,607 --> 01:27:34,109
The Angel of Verdun.

1293
01:27:44,995 --> 01:27:46,121
Okay.

1294
01:27:55,630 --> 01:27:56,923
<i>It's a new day, people!</i>

1295
01:27:57,424 --> 01:27:58,550
Destiny calls.

1296
01:27:59,092 --> 01:28:01,428
The world expects only one thing from us:

1297
01:28:01,428 --> 01:28:02,470
That we will win!

1298
01:28:02,637 --> 01:28:04,597
Rest assured they enemy will thank you

1299
01:28:04,597 --> 01:28:06,308
for not giving a hundred percent today

1300
01:28:06,683 --> 01:28:07,517
Squad!

1301
01:28:10,895 --> 01:28:12,022
Where's J Squad?

1302
01:28:30,665 --> 01:28:31,583
Right, okay.

1303
01:28:31,583 --> 01:28:34,127
So this Omega, it controls time?

1304
01:28:34,336 --> 01:28:36,588
Exploding it into pieces and sending
its bullocks back to where it came from!

1305
01:28:36,796 --> 01:28:37,797
And then we go home!

1306
01:28:38,798 --> 01:28:40,091
Right, it's guarded by an Alpha...

1307
01:28:40,133 --> 01:28:41,760
Just kill it, okay?

1308
01:28:42,302 --> 01:28:43,219
No!

1309
01:28:43,386 --> 01:28:45,013
You head what Cage said.

1310
01:28:45,055 --> 01:28:46,264
Do not kill an Alpha.

